^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Let's first discuss the bidding. Why do I think Bonnie should bid 1H instead of doubling?|
PG| ***** 24 ***** |


AT| In general, it is better to show a 5-card suit with an overcall. On this hand in particular, Bonnie's hearts are so good and spades so weak, it is particularly clear. But even if we changed her hand around a little bit so that she had say @SKxxx @HAQxxx I would still recommend she bid 1H.|
PG| ***** 25 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|In competitive auctions, informing your partner you have a 5-card suit usually works best. On occasion, such as this hand, you might miss a 4-4 fit. But on many of those hands partner will have 3 hearts, so no big deal as you play in your 8-card fit. So the only risk you run is if partner has 2 or fewer hearts and exactly 4 spades.|
PG| ***** 26 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If pard has 5 spades they can bid spades anyway - that happens rarely. Moreover, the advantage of knowing the 5-card suit, so you can apply the LOTT, works out much better more often. Imagine if Joan had even 2 hearts and say weaker spades like Kxxx. I would still rather play in hearts with AKQxx opposite xx than 2S with Kxxx opposite xxxx.|
